Dictionary.Description: A particular thing that somebody does
A projection on a rotating part in machinery, designed to make sliding contact with another part while rotating and impart reciprocal or variable motion to it
All the people who act in a play or film
A small domesticated carnivorous mammal with soft fur, a short snout, and retractable claws; it is widely kept as a pet or for catching mice
A wound caused by something sharp
A tall upright post, spar, or other structure on a ship or boat, in sailing vessels generally carrying a sail or sails
A piece of coarse material placed on a floor for people to wipe their feet on
A dishonest scheme to gain money or possessions from someone fraudulently, especially a complex or prolonged one
A particular amount of money
An increase in the amount of something, especially in wealth or weight
A clear alcoholic spirit distilled from grain or malt and flavoured with juniper berries
A pub, typically one in the country, in some cases providing accommodation
A type of flat bread found in the cuisines (= cooking styles) of many parts of Asia
A person's sense of self-esteem or self-importance
A person who is preoccupied with his or her own interests; a selfish person
Abstract strategy board game for two players in which the aim is to capture more territory than the opponent by fencing off empty space invented in China
A group of similar things that belong together in some way
An area of ground on which a town, building, or monument is constructed
A procedure intended to establish the quality, performance, or reliability of something, especially before it is taken into widespread use
A long, narrow piece of cloth worn around the neck, especially by men, with a knot in front
A small songbird that searches acrobatically for insects among foliage and branches
Any of the five digits at the end of the human foot
A young child
A hoofed grazing or browsing animal, with branched bony antlers that are shed annually and typically borne only by the male
Of a colour at the end of the spectrum next to orange and opposite violet, as of blood, fire, or rubies
A tall, slender-leaved plant of the grass family, which grows in water or on marshy ground
Set again or differently
Cease work or movement in order to relax, sleep, or recover strength
The unit of reproduction of a flowering plant, capable of developing into another such plant
A person of supposed supernatural insight who sees visions of the future
A group of similar things that belong together in some way
A woody perennial plant, typically having a single stem or trunk growing to a considerable height and bearing lateral branches at some distance from the ground
